message: Your voices were heard! The GOP caved on their scheme to weaken the Office of Congressional Ethics. Thanks to those who called!
Always exciting to begin a new term despite the concerns I have. I'm dedicated to preventing the unraveling of the progress we've made, while moving forward in the areas we care about.
Since the Affordable Care Act, the number of uninsured in the San Diego region has been nearly cut in half. Repeal would mean nearly 300,000 in our region would lose access to health care. #ACAWorks
Meet your House Democratic Women of the 115th Congress. Ready to get things done!
I'm hearing from constituents concerned about a repeal of the Affordable Care Act, including a mom with a pre-existing condition who's worried about her family. #ACAWorks
Ending door delivery of mail would hurt customers, businesses, and the Postal Service. My bipartisan resolution in the House will help protect this vital service.
The integrity of our election process is paramount. There needs to be a thorough investigation into Russian influence on the 2016 election.
Proper vetting is critical. The American people have the right to have a full understanding of those who will be working for them.

Thank you President Obama for your service to the nation. Thank you for fighting for working families by creating 16 million jobs, expanding health care to 20 million people, and staying true to our values that we hold dear as Americans.

Chicano Park, a symbol of the strength of our diversity, has been designated a National Historic Landmark. Proud to join with Congressman Juan Vargas in his effort to help make this designation a reality.
Constituents continue to contact me fearful of an ACA repeal. I opposed the GOP budget resolution that sets a repeal in motion.
I'm honored to again participate in this year's Human Trafficking Awareness Rally. We have to do everything we can to protect our young people and prosecute those who traffic victims!
Holding a press conference with Rep. Scott Peters and constituents to put a face on what ACA repeal means. #ACAWorks #SavetheACA

1100 strong at MLK breakfast this morning to celebrate his legacy and carry on his work. Let's all come together today in memory of  Martin Luther King, Jr. We have achieved much in his honor but have more to accomplish today in fighting for equality for all.
Sad and yet honored to look back at the best mentor ever in Lucy Killea.  Enjoyed our chat over the Christmas holiday with her sense of humor and always classy keen intellect.

As many of you know I am attending the inauguration. It's not to honor or support the incoming president. It's in respect of the peaceful transfer of power that is paramount to our democracy. Bearing witness to that is part of the way I interpret my role as a Representative. I'll also be in participating in the Women's March tomorrow to show the president and his team that they must represent all Americans, regardless of gender, ethnicity, race, religion or sexual orientation.
Further proof that we need a full and independent investigation into Russian involvement. I'm pushing legislation to do just that.
Recent poll shows #7in10 Americans support #RoevWade. Fight for this right becomes more critical than ever before!
Proud to join with women from #SanDiego & the country in DC for the discussion & fight for women's issues, equality for all! #WomensMarch
Instead of creating jobs or raising wages, the president's first act is a step to take healthcare from 20M Americans.
Reinstating the global gag rule is a threat to women’s health around the world. Studies have shows that access to family planning services actually reduces incidents of abortion.

Many of my constituents have cases before the federal government regarding VA benefits, Social Security, Medicare, etc. The President's move not only hurts federal employees in our region but the constituents who rely on those workers.

So proud of my former colleague Patrick Kennedy for his leadership. The Future of Mental Health Forum brought experts and the public together to fight for and champion critical issues that effect our lives every day.  Thank you Patrick.

A border wall is a simplistic approach to a complex problem. A wall will cost billions to build. Millions more tax dollars will be spent on eminent domain lawsuits as Americans fight to keep their property from being seized by the federal government. Only bipartisan comprehensive immigration reform is going solve the problem of illegal immigration.

As we memorialize the millions of Holocaust victims and celebrate the resilience of survivors and their families let us renew our embrace of moral values and the commitment we made as a nation to be a land of opportunity for the world's most vulnerable. #HolocaustRemeberanceDay

America has always been a beacon of hope and freedom around the world. This executive order slams the door on those seeking refuge from violence and oppression and runs contrary to the values that have defined America for generations. The Muslim ban is a policy based on fear not strength. This will simply reduce the stature and influence America will have globally.
Federal courts have rightly stayed President Trump's unconstitutional executive order banning Muslims and refugees. Immigration officials need to follow and respect the rule of the federal judges.

Today I contacted Customs and Border Protection to demand information on anyone being held at San Diego's airport and that they be released immediately. If you, or someone you know, are detained at the airport or traveling abroad with a visa or green card, please contact my office at (619) 280-5353 or (202) 225-2040 so that we can provide assistance.
Last chance to get covered with Covered California. Deadline to enroll in a health plan is today at midnight. #GetCovered
This should never happen in America. A constituent of mine was crossing the border into San Diego when he was singled out for having brown skin.

I’m honored and excited to become the Ranking Democrat on the Higher Education and Workforce Training Subcommittee. Education policy has always been a passion of mine and I’m excited to work with my colleagues on increasing higher education opportunities for all!
I went on Fox 5 in San Diego to talk about Democrats' fight to stop Trump’s Executive Order banning refugees.
Black History Month is a time to celebrate the lasting contributions African Americans have made to America and renew our commitment to the pursuit of justice and equality.

Our values, our democracy, and our security won the day with the judge’s decision to put a nationwide hold on the President’s ban on refugees and Muslims. The President needs to rescind his immoral and unconstitutional executive order. As long as it remains, I will continue to pursue efforts in Congress to repeal it.
Schools deserve help in their efforts to keep our kids safe. I'll be re-introducing my bill to provide federal funds to train educators to identify trafficking.
Blocking the public's access to info on animal welfare is unacceptable. The Dept of Agriculture should reinstate the webpage immediately.
President Obama worked with states and local educators to create protections that ensure quality teachers for our kids. I led the opposition against ending these protections.
We should be making it easier for Americans to vote, not harder. I introduced two bills that will increase access to the ballot and protect the integrity of our elections.
Was the executive order advancing our safety?  Good to see courts again say "No." This is grateful relief for those heavily vetted and wanting to bring their talents to our country.
Protecting ACA, Social Security & Medicare, pushing back on Trump. My priorities laid out in my interview here:
Congress has a responsibility to follow all the threads to reveal what this means to our national security and our democracy.

The resignation of Michael Flynn underscores the increasing and disturbing potential of Russia’s grip on the White House. It’s another instance of someone in the Administration, the other being the President himself, who could potentially be subject to blackmail by the Russian government. There needs to be an outside, bipartisan, and independent investigation into Russian influence in the White House.
Proud of my city for joining us in this fight and standing up for our values that have always made America great.
Instead of taking pensions away from Americans - as House GOP is doing today - we should be voting for a independent investigation into the White House.
When is enough going to be enough for my GOP colleagues to allow a vote on independent investigation of the White House?
America needs a Labor Secretary who is going to put workers first, and Andrew Puzder was not that person. I raised serious concerns about his nomination in a letter to the Senate.
Two-state solution is the most credible way to achieve lasting peace.

Congratulations to San Diego State University on their recent recognition as a National Model Undergraduate Entrepreneurship Program for 2017 by the United States Association for Small Business and Entrepreneurship (USASBE). I'm so proud to have such an asset in my district.
Proud of my Democratic colleagues’ effort on Ways & Means Committee to get the President’s taxes. The American people have a right to know.
Trump needs to end the censorship on animal welfare information.
Those who sacrifice for us shouldn’t struggle to put food on the table. I reintroduced my bipartisan bill extending food assistance to military families.

Community health clinics are a vital resource for families. Repeal of the healthcare law would have a devastating impact on their ability to provide health services. I joined with the dedicated people who run these clinics to #ProtectOurCare.

There's a new family health clinic in El Cajon. Repeal of the healthcare law would hurt the ability of community health centers in our region, such as this one, to provide services to the thousands of families that rely on them.
I don’t always agree with Senator McCain, but here I do. Our independent press is a pillar of our democracy. #NotTheEnemy
Miss him yet? #PresidentsDay
Just on KUSI talking military hunger, refugee and Muslim ban, and the rise in anti-semitism in our country.
Hope you can make it to my town hall meeting on March 11! Click below for details and to RSVP.

As the new ranking member of the Higher Education Subcommittee, I wanted to hear the voices of local education leaders on how to approach improving our higher education system. We have an amazing turnout for my Higher Education Roundtable! I look forward to working with local education leaders and constituents on how we can make a degree more affordable and accessible.

Holding a press conference with local immigration advocates to denounce Trump’s anti-immigration actions. Immigrants add to our rich heritage and are an economic benefit. According to a study, mass deportation would cost our economy over $2 trillion in lost GDP. His policies are only going to hurt families, our economy, and won’t make us safe. #RefugeesWelcome #ImmigrantsWelcome

Thank you for the overwhelming interest in my town hall meeting! It has reached capacity at the 1,200 seat venue. I'll be looking to live stream the meeting for those who can't attend.  You can always email me or call with specific issues. I want to hear from you!
Shame on Trump for rescinding protections for transgender students. As a member of the Congressional LGBT Equality Caucus, I will keep fighting to #ProtectTransKids.
Proud of my perfect score. Thank you League of Conservation Voters for all you do for the environment. I'll keep fighting for clean air, clean water, and open spaces more than ever.

The American people have a right to know about the President’s financial ties with Russia. I’m cosponsoring Rep. Nadler’s resolution to order the release of Trump’s taxes and expose the truth. The GOP can try to bury this issue but it won’t go away.
Thank you to the advocates who came out and for all you do for our immigrant community. We will keep working toward a humane approach to comprehensive immigration reform.
People are hungry for action and don't like the direction of their country. I sat down with KPBS to talk about resisting Trump, protecting our health care, and comprehensive immigration reform.

This latest report of the White House pressuring the FBI to comment on a pending investigation can be added to a list – a list that keeps growing – of reasons to have a full, bipartisan and independent investigation.
Meeting with just a few of the many members of Indivisible from the 53rd district.  Thank you for staying engaged with your government!
Stories of immigrants contributing to America are a millionfold. Immigrants should be valued not scorned or demonized.
Just voted with House Democrats to force Trump to release 10 years of taxes, but we were blocked by GOP. American people deserve the truth. We are not going away.

Lots of constituent meetings in DC today! Always glad to see our local Letter Carriers at my door. We're working together on my Door Delivery bill (H. Res. 28) which has 138 bipartisan cosponsors and counting!
Proud to lead the effort of #WomenWearWhite to honor the women before us who struggled for equal rights. Watch as we stand out in the House tonight.

Honored to have Quinn Dang, daughter to Vietnamese refugees, as my guest to the President’s speech to Congress. Democrats filled the House chamber with immigrants and refugees to resist Trump’s anti-immigrant and anti-refugee policies and remind him that America must always be a safe haven for those fleeing oppression.

What we heard tonight was not the inspiring call to action that is needed. The president’s attempt at unifying the nation fell flat. The divisive rhetoric he has used over the past years is not going to be healed by a few words in a speech.

Thanks Tom Karlo, Nancy Worlie of KPBS and Kathleen Rae for coming to DC to talk about the importance of KPBS to our region. I'll be fighting to maintain federal funding to keep public radio and television on the air.
In his first 40 days, President Obama moved to save 4 million jobs. The only jobs this President has created is to give cabinet spots to billionaires. #WhereAreTheJobs
The refugees seeking entry today share the same hopes and dreams as Quinn's parents did - to build a better life and contribute back to the community.
An Attorney General who needs to recuse himself on an investigation this important should not lead the Department of Justice.
Military families, LVC score, Trump's taxes, & more are in my latest E-News. Sign up to have it sent to your inbox.
Led my Democratic colleagues on the House Committee on Education and the Workforce to urge Education Secretary Betsy DeVos to take concrete steps to ensure the safety of #trans student

As ranking member of the Higher Education Subcommittee, I will resist any attempt by Trump to weaken our education system. I appreciate the school leaders and students who shared their higher education visions at my roundtable.

Yesterday, these two young ladies shared their heartfelt personal stories. Joined by their teachers and the American Friends Service Committee, we talked about ending the use of for-profit prisons and judicial reform. President Obama made progress in this area only to see it being reversed by this administration.
Looking forward to honoring fallen hero Officer Jonathan "J.D." De Guzman this morning.
Latest #refugee and #MuslimBan is unjust, unnecessary, and unconstitutional. #RefugeesWelcome
Inspiring to see the community to come together to honor JD. Proud to carry the bill that made the “Jonathan ‘J.D.’ De Guzman Post Office Building” a reality.
After having their healthcare repeal bill under lock and key, refusing to let anyone read it, the GOP have finally freed the bill. After looking at it, I think they should have kept it hidden.
My office is fully decked out for #InternationalWomensDay. Celebrating women in America and around the world. Thank you to everyone who sent me the postcards!
The Consumer Financial Protection Bureau (CFPB) has saved consumers $12 billion. Great explainer on why we must protect this effective agency.
On #InternationalWomensDay I offered an amendment to preserve access to women's preventive health, maternity care, and direct access to an OBGYN.
Trump’s immigration policies are making us less safe. Only comprehensive immigration reform will solve illegal immigration.
America’s future success depends on a quality higher education system. Here are my priorities as Ranking Member of Higher Ed Subcommittee.
We need to keep guns away from those who should not have them. GOP/Trump are rolling back those efforts, which I’m resisting.
The American people are demanding the truth. The American people deserve the truth. #FollowTheFacts

I will be live streaming my town hall meeting on my Facebook page tomorrow Saturday, March 11 at 10 AM.
My town hall meeting is coming to you live from Montezuma Hall at San Diego State University.
With our schools facing tight budgets, this bill will make a bad situation worse. We need to invest in all our children's future.
It is clear the Republican healthcare repeal will hurt more people than it will help. The CBO reports their bill will result in 24 million Americans losing access to healthcare.
I hear from constituents everyday who are afraid of losing their healthcare coverage. I'll keep fighting to #ProtectOurCare.
The President promised insurance for everybody yet he's pushing the GOP #PayMoreForLess bill that will kick 24 million Americans off their health insurance.
Once again the courts have blocked the President's illegal refugee and Muslim ban - a ban that's based on fear not strength that will ultimately make us less safe.
The Marines United scandal is abhorrent and the perpetrators must be prosecuted. I'll be pressing the Marine Corps for accountability.

The President’s reckless budget will be met with fierce resistance in Congress.  Here are a few of low lights:  $4 billion in cuts to Pell Grants meaning fewer high school students will be able to go to college.  $6 billion in cuts to NIH, hurting San Diego and the lifesaving medical research done in our region.  Nearly $3 billion in job training, meaning a weaker American workforce.  Nearly $4 billion in teacher training and after-school and summer programs.  Nearly $10 billion in education.  Cuts President Obama’s entire Clean Power Plan to combat climate change.
Juror discrimination on the basis of race, color, religion, sex, national origin, and economic status is already prohibited. It’s time that the LGBT community be free of such discrimination.
This administration continues to roll back key protections for our most vulnerable students. I promise to fight these efforts and ask for hearings on ways to protect student borrowers.
The American people are not on board. Only 24% support Trumpcare. #ACAWorks #ProtectOurCare
Under Trump plan being a woman would be a pre-existing condition again, meaning higher premiums for women than men.

Promising to hear the FBI is investigating Russian hacking of 2016 election. Also need an independent commission to get to the truth. FBI Director Comey also says no evidence of Trump’s claim of wiretapping. Trump owes an apology to President Obama and the American people.
Looking forward to my first hearing as Ranking Member of the Higher Education Subcommittee to find ways to make college more affordable. You can watch it here.

I'm honored to be a guest at the Healthcare Town Hall with Assemblymember Todd Gloria and State Senators Toni Atkins and Dr. Ed Hernandez this Saturday. For more information about the event click here.
TrumpCare will be coming up for a vote in the House of Representatives on Thursday. I will be voting NO in order to #ProtectOurCare.
Thrilled to talk track with four time Olympian and nine time Olympic gold medalist Carl Lewis.

Thanks to #militarymonday blog for highlighting my fix to end hunger among our military families.
Proud to join the Opportunity Youth panel today to ensure young people have an accessible pathway into our workforce. There is an immense return for every dollar that we invest in our nation’s youth.

Congrats Kyle, Christina, and Angelica on winning the Congressional App Challenge for California's 53rd Congressional District! Their winning app helps students stay organized and keep up with school work.
Trump signed away your Internet privacy rights, which can now be sold to the highest bidder.
Hearing from victims of the Marines United photo scandal. Those responsible must be held accountable.
American people have the right to know the President will put them before profits. I #DemandAVote to force Trump to release his tax returns.
Meet the faces of the local resistance. Proud to meet with our local building trade unions who Wednesday held up #resist signs during Trump's speech.
I need your opinion! My latest survey is on Trump's taxes and the Supreme Court. You can also see the results of my previous survey.

Celebrating 20 years of the Hillcrest Farmers Market!

Immigration and judicial policies based on fear make us less safe. We need faith not fear.
The GOP should be working with Democrats to build on the successes of the ACA instead of risking healthcare access for millions of Americans.

#earthday2017 has new significance with Trump rolling back environmental protections. My oped in San Diego UptownNews on how I’m resisting.
We will #neverforget the 11 million, including 6 million Jews, who perished in the Holocaust.

I called on Education Secretary DeVos to ensure we are honoring loan forgiveness to those who agree to a career in public service, such as in areas of education, military, or public health. We should be encouraging people to engage in public service careers.
73% of Americans want an independent investigation. It’s time pass the Protect our Democracy Act to create bipartisan commission to #FollowTheFacts.
The more the American people hear about the GOP health care bill the less they like about it. Time for Republicans to work with Democrats to build on the ACA.

Congrats to the students who entered my Congressional Art Competition, but especially to the winner Heyju Cho of Mater Dei High School. Her piece is called "True leader" and it will hang in the Capitol Complex.
Even in retirement these teachers never stop fighting for educators and students! Thanks for stopping by my office today.

I was extremely honored to receive the National Alliance for Partnerships in Equity (NAPE) Legislator of the Year award and meet with NAPE representatives from the Sweetwater Union High School District.

Trump could’ve spent first 100 days working together to help American families. Instead we’ve gotten chaos, confusion and broken promises.

Making your voices heard has made a difference.  Funding bill has many of our priorities - NIH increase, funding for Planned Parenthood and year-round Pell Grants. And no money wasted on a border wall.
Each year, there are an estimated 8,000 to 11,000 victims of sex trafficking in San Diego County. My bill will help schools train educators to spot the signs of trafficking to keep our kids safe.
San Diego gets about $800 million in NIH funding each year. Proud to lead the effort to get a $2 billion increase in this year's budget.
There's no such thing as a good shutdown. Government shutdowns hurt families, hurt seniors, hurt our veterans, and hurt our military.
Thanks for the calls and stories. My NO vote on #TrumpCare will be for you and constituents like Elizabeth & Tim, whose pre-existing conditions will mean higher premiums.

I'm cosponsoring HR 356 to create a independent commission to #followthefacts on Russia. This bill should be brought to the floor for a vote when the House is back in session next week.
A win for the climate change fight. Credit the American people for making their voices heard. #ActOnClimate

Investments in life-saving medical research are critical to finding cures and impacts our local economy. Hosted a panel of experts today to discuss what Trump's proposed cuts to the NIH will mean for our region.
Pell Grants have meant access to a college degree for millions of low-income students. Introduced a bill to ensure the program’s stability and its purchasing power into the future.
When will enough be enough for my GOP colleagues? They’re the key to whether we have an independent investigation into the Trump/Russia connection.
Proud to be up early with Team Davis racing with other government officials and members of the media in the ACLI Capital Challenge.

Thanks to Franklin Elementary students for making these Mothers Day cards for our servicewomen who are away from their own families serving our country!

No question Robert Mueller can lead a competent investigation into Trump/Russia connection. It's still critical that congressional investigations move forward and an independent commission is established.
Multiple moves can be disruptive and create stress for military families. I'm co-lead on a bill to give military families flexibility on how relocation works best for them.
I look forward to hearing from you at my next town hall meeting. It will be on Monday, June 19 from 6pm - 7:30pm. Click below for details.
Successful investments in our priorities are thanks to the voice of the people. I will continue to fight for what's important for our communities.
I feel for the families devastated by what happened in Manchester.

Yet another reason for an independent investigation. I signed a discharge petition to force a vote to create a commission to conduct one.

The Marines United website was a disgusting breach of trust. Proud to support the PRIVATE Act to update the Uniform Code of Military Justice to prohibit the wrongful distribution of nude or pornographic images.
Not all veterans get their healthcare from the VA. Trump slashing $800 billion from Medicaid jeopardizes health coverage of 1.7 million veterans.
Trump cutting nearly 20% from the budget of the National Institutes of Health will hurt San Diego’s economy and life-saving medical research.
New CBO score says 23 million Americans will be uninsured if Trumpcare becomes law. That's unacceptable.
When Trump says the Affordable Care Act is imploding, he really means he’s imploding it. I joined 195 of my House colleagues to demand that Trump continue to fund the ACA.
Trump's budget abandons our commitment to public education. Our children's future is at stake. #TrumpCuts

10th Anniversary of Sophie's Lemonade Stand and her last year raising money for Leukemia research. With young people like this - our future is bright

On Memorial Day, it is inspiring to see San Diegans and Americans come together to honor those who answered the call to defend our country and made the ultimate sacrifice. Today is an opportunity to share memories and celebrate their lives.

A sustainable planet is key to our future. Withdrawing from the Paris Agreement will hurt our environment and our economy. San Diego is a leader in solar energy, which is responsible for thousands of jobs. Withdrawal puts that at risk.

A victory for voting rights. I’ll keep pushing for bills to further protect voting rights, including my Universal Vote by Mail Act.

During the Great Recession, my office helped hundreds of constituents who were afraid of losing their homes. Instead of working to improve the financial security of the American people, the GOP is pushing to end consumer protections put in place to prevent it from happening again. Millions suffered during the recession. Let’s not repeat history.
Former FBI Director James Comey will testify tomorrow before the Senate Intelligence Committee, which posted his opening statement. You can read it here.

While Comey testifies in the Senate, the House GOP will be repealing the Dodd-Frank financial consumer protections. Repeal will allow Wall Street to run fast and loose with your money, putting the financial security of the American people at risk.
Repealing Dodd-Frank would gut the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau, ending the office tasked with protecting consumers, including student borrowers from predatory lending practices.

Today we confirmed the President’s disturbing behavior into the Flynn/Russia investigation. With each passing day, it’s clear we need to dig deeper. In addition to the investigations by Congress and the Special Counsel, we need an independent commission to get to the truth for the American people.

Need help with a federal agency? My staff will be holding an East County Office Hours on Monday, June 12 form 2-8pm at the El Cajon Library. These East County Office Hours will be held every second Monday of every month.

Inspiring to see mayors and governors filling Trump’s leadership void on the Paris Agreement. My colleagues and I in Congress will do all we can to support them.
With my friend and former House colleague Gabby Giffords before the commissioning of the USS Gabrielle Giffords in Galveston, which is due to arrive in San Diego in 20 days.
